Document: AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzerInstance  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectspectrumanalyzerinstance.rst  
Summary: A class for analyzing audio spectra in real-time within Godot's audio processing pipeline.  

Inherits: AudioEffect < AudioFilter < AudioNode < Node < Object  
This class provides functionality to capture and analyze frequency data from audio signals. It is typically used in conjunction with AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzer to visualize or process spectral information. Key Rule: This class must be attached to an AudioBus to function.  

Properties:  
- `fft_size (int)`: Size of the Fast Fourier Transform buffer. Larger values increase frequency resolution but consume more memory. Default: 1024.  
- `update_rate (float)`: Frequency at which the spectrum is updated (in Hz). Default: 60.  
- `spectrum (Array<float>)`: Read-only array containing the current frequency spectrum data.  

Methods:  
- `get_spectrum() -> Array<float>`: Returns the latest frequency spectrum data as an array of float values.  
- `set_fft_size(size: int)`: Sets the FFT buffer size. Must be a power of two between 32 and 8192.  
- `set_update_rate(rate: float)`: Sets the spectrum update rate in Hz. Must be greater than 0.  

Note: The spectrum data is normalized to a range of 0.0 (silence) to 1.0 (maximum amplitude).  
Warning: High FFT sizes may cause performance issues on low-end hardware.  
Tip: Use this class with AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzer for real-time visualization of audio frequencies.  

GDScript:  
```gdscript  
var analyzer = AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzerInstance.new()  
analyzer.fft_size = 2048  
analyzer.update_rate = 120  
```
