Document: AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzerInstance
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectspectrumanalyzerinstance.rst
Summary: The get_magnitude_for_frequency_range method and MagnitudeMode enumeration for analyzing audio frequency ranges.

MagnitudeMode enum:
- MAGNITUDE_AVERAGE (0): Use the average value across the frequency range as magnitude
- MAGNITUDE_MAX (1): Use the maximum value of the frequency range as magnitude

Method: get_magnitude_for_frequency_range(from_hz: float, to_hz: float, mode: MagnitudeMode = 1) → Vector2
Returns the magnitude of frequencies from from_hz to to_hz in linear energy as a Vector2. The x component represents the left stereo channel, y represents the right channel. The mode parameter determines processing: 0 for average value calculation, 1 for maximum value selection. Default mode is MAGNITUDE_MAX (1).